tcmTable.name: tcmTable
tcmTable.description: This table contains the hardware information for the Timing Control Module (TCM) s.

tcmEntry.name: tcmEntry
tcmEntry.description: This table entry contains the hardware information for a single Timing Control Module (TCM) .

tcmIndex.name: tcmIndex
tcmIndex.description: This is the index for this Timing Control Module (TCM) .

tcmHwType.name: tcmHwType
tcmHwType.description: This is the type for this Timing Control Module (TCM) .

tcmHwVersion.name: tcmHwVersion
tcmHwVersion.description: This is the version for this Timing Control Module (TCM) .

tcmPllStatus.name: tcmPllStatus
tcmPllStatus.description: This is the phase-locked loop (PLL) status for this Timing Control Module (TCM) .

tcmOperationStatus.name: tcmOperationStatus
tcmOperationStatus.description: This is the operation status of the clock output for this Timing Control Module (TCM). The status is enabled if the switch is configured to use TCM for timing and disabled otherwise.

tcmCurrentTimingRef.name: tcmCurrentTimingRef
tcmCurrentTimingRef.description: This is the current timing reference in use for this Timing Control Module (TCM) .

tcmRequestedTimingMode.name: tcmRequestedTimingMode
tcmRequestedTimingMode.description: This is the timing reference requested to be used for this Timing Control Module (TCM) .

tcmOperatingTimingMode.name: tcmOperatingTimingMode
tcmOperatingTimingMode.description: This is the operating timing mode, which can be different from the requested timing mode if mode failover is enabled.

tcmModeFailover.name: tcmModeFailover
tcmModeFailover.description: This is the modefailover that causes the Timing Control Module (TCM) to automatically switch between timing modes (for example external to line) if it is enabled.

tcmPrimaryRefSource.name: tcmPrimaryRefSource
tcmPrimaryRefSource.description: This is the primary timing reference source for this Timing Control Module (TCM) .

tcmSecondaryRefSource.name: tcmSecondaryRefSource
tcmSecondaryRefSource.description: This is the secondary timing reference source for this Timing Control Module (TCM) .

tcmBitsFramingFormat.name: tcmBitsFramingFormat
tcmBitsFramingFormat.description: This is the framing format of the BITS interface for this Timing Control Module (TCM) .

tcmBitsCodingFormat.name: tcmBitsCodingFormat
tcmBitsCodingFormat.description: This is the coding format of the BITS interface for this Timing Control Module (TCM) .

tcmBitsOutputLevel.name: tcmBitsOutputLevel
tcmBitsOutputLevel.description: This is the output level (dB) of the DS1 BITS interface for this Timing Control Module (TCM) .

tcmRevertiveSwitching.name: tcmRevertiveSwitching
tcmRevertiveSwitching.description: This is the status of the revertive switching for timing sources on this Timing Control Module (TCM) .

tcmRevertiveDelay.name: tcmRevertiveDelay
tcmRevertiveDelay.description: This is the amount of time after the restoration of the primary timing reference before the Timing Control Module (TCM) will be instructed to return to the primary timing reference. This value is truncated to whole seconds.

tcmFailoverDelay.name: tcmFailoverDelay
tcmFailoverDelay.description: This is the amount of time after the failure of a timing reference before the Timing Control Module (TCM) will be instructed to switch to the next available timing reference. This value is truncated to whole seconds.

tcmReferenceTable.name: tcmReferenceTable
tcmReferenceTable.description: This table contains the timing reference source information for the Timing Control Module (TCM) .

tcmReferenceEntry.name: tcmReferenceEntry
tcmReferenceEntry.description: This table entry contains the timing reference source information for a single Timing Control Module (TCM) .

tcmRefSource.name: tcmRefSource
tcmRefSource.description: This is the timing reference source index for the Timing Control Module (TCM) .

tcmRefSourceText.name: tcmRefSourceText
tcmRefSourceText.description: This is a textual description of the timing reference source that is provided to the Timing Control Module (TCM).

tcmRefSourceStatus.name: tcmRefSourceStatus
tcmRefSourceStatus.description: This is the status of the timing reference source that is provided to the Timing Control Module (TCM).

tcmRefSourceAdminStatus.name: tcmRefSourceAdminStatus
tcmRefSourceAdminStatus.description: This is the admin status of the timing reference source that is provided to the Timing Control Module (TCM).

tcmRefSourceQualStatus.name: tcmRefSourceQualStatus
tcmRefSourceQualStatus.description: This is the RefQual status of the timing reference source that is provided to the Timing Control Module (TCM) .

tcmTxBits1RefSource.name: tcmTxBits1RefSource
tcmTxBits1RefSource.description: This object is the timing source that is used to derive DS1 or E1 signal transmitted out on the BITS1 interface.

tcmTxBits2RefSource.name: tcmTxBits2RefSource
tcmTxBits2RefSource.description: This object is the timing source that is used to derive DS1 or E1 signal transmitted out on the BITS2 interface.

tcmTxBitsOperMode.name: tcmTxBitsOperMode
tcmTxBitsOperMode.description: This object refers to the mode of operation for the derived DS1 or E1 outputs. In thresholdAIS mode, AIS is transmitted on the derived DS1 or E1 signal when the transmit reference source becomes unacceptable. In automatic mode, synchronization status messages are passed through on the derived DS1 or E1 output if SSM Automatic Reference Switching is enabled and the DS1 or E1 frame format supports SSM. Otherwise, AIS is transmitted when the reference becomes unacceptable.

tcmTimingSourceChange.name: tcmTimingSourceChange
tcmTimingSourceChange.description: This trap is generated whenever the Timing Control Module (TCM) timing source (tcmCurrentTimingRef) is changed either manually or by the system due to failure detection.

tcmTimingSourceFailed.name: tcmTimingSourceFailed
tcmTimingSourceFailed.description: This trap is generated whenever the Timing Control Module (TCM) timing source (tcmCurrentTimingRef) fails.
